    <!-- Guide Window -->
    <sys:String x:Key="TxtGuideTitle">Guide</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="TxtGuideHeader">How to use Optiscaler Manager</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="TxtGuideHeaderDesc">Simple steps to enhance your games</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="TxtGuideStep1Title">1. Find your games</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="TxtGuideStep1Desc">Click the 'Scan Games' button to let the app automatically find installed games from Steam, Epic, GOG, or Xbox. Check the 'Add Manually' button if you have a standalone game.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="TxtGuideStep2Title">2. Manage a game</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="TxtGuideStep2Desc">Next to your game in the list, click 'Manage'. A window will open allowing you to install or update the OptiScaler mod for that specific game.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="TxtGuideStep3Title">3. Install OptiScaler</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="TxtGuideStep3Desc">Inside the Management window, choose your OptiScaler version and options. Use 'Auto Install' for a quick setup. If Auto Install fails or cannot find the correct executable (.exe), use 'Manual Install' to select the game's executable yourself.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="TxtGuideStep4Title">4. Play the game</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="TxtGuideStep4Desc">Once installed, start your game normally. Inside the game, bring up the OptiScaler menu using the 'Insert' key to tweak your settings!</sys:String>

